# Docker build context filter for hexa-lang.
# The runner image only needs:
#   - build/hexa_linux_<arch>           (CLI dispatcher, arm64 + x86_64)
#   - build/hexa_interp_linux_<arch>    (stage0/interp, arm64 + x86_64)
# Everything else just bloats the upload to the buildx daemon.

# Default: ignore everything…
*

# …then re-include the precise paths the Dockerfile COPY'es.
!build/hexa_linux_arm64
!build/hexa_linux_x86_64
!build/hexa_interp_linux_arm64
!build/hexa_interp_linux_x86_64
!docker/
# 2026-04-26: bake module_loader + stdlib so bind-mount-less containers
# can resolve `use "stdlib/X"` (raw#92 fail-loud gap closure).
!self/
!self/module_loader.hexa
!self/stdlib/
!self/stdlib/**
# 2026-04-26 ω-runner-7: include native_gate.c so the builder stage can
# compile native_gate.so and bake LD_PRELOAD into the runtime image
# (raw#7 OS-level enforce; macOS host stays advisory due to SIP, Linux
# container is the actual enforcer per Mac→docker hard-landing policy).
!self/native/
!self/native/native_gate.c

# Keep .git out — multi-MB and never needed by the runner image.
.git/
